column2: i laid in bed and cried for 4 days. i thought my mothering/birthing part of my life was over. but on the fifth day i got really bored with myself and i got up & i started writing a book. since that time i've written a second book. i've created goddess circles for women  in shelters and in the community. i painted a lot of goddess art which i eventually turned into an oracle deck. i studied the chakra system and reiki & went through the certification to become a reiki master. i've been opened in so many ways because of my willingness to be open. the goddess in so many of her forms & my spirit guides have come in & taught me how to do oracle readings and shamanic healing practices utilizing reiki to help people remember their light.  someone said to me a while back when i didn't even understand
column4: you are a witch healer. now i see. we can only be what we are. it will emerge. give it the sacred space. trust it. i have only love for calling myself a witch. for i know what it truly means and that is to see and channel the light for myself and others. â˜‰ birthing is a woman's ancient gift. its eternally boundless. remember. .

column3: but you are not damaged. you are more than what was done to you.

column1: 236276;instagram;2018-11-09 17:53:58;FALSE;"i had a huge epiphany the other day!
i was thinking about my past and the sexual abuse that happened to me. i remembered a family member asking me why i never pressed charges on the person who abused me. (there were several men
column2: i only know who one of the people was.)

column1: i carried a bit of guilt
column2: shame and condemnation for not doing that.

column1: but this week i realized... ""hey! why didn't they protect me and press charges? why do i have to carry their weight and judgment when
column3: i should have been protected from being abused. and someone should have noticed the abuse happening. they should have pressed charges)

column1: i have had years of healing yet i am so grateful for this revelation! god is always speaking and helping me see me through his eyes. thank you lord!
if this is part of your story too...it is not your fault! keep seeking hope and truth in your healing!
(note: the abuser that i knew who he was has passed away. so he can no longer hurt others.)

column2: etc. being a decent human being should be a minimum requirement. i am ready to take sides. i am striving to be an advocate for historically marginalized people. i should be using my privilege to help dismantle the systems that put children at risk

column1: as some of you might be wondering
column2: i was away and been missing for the whole week. reason being that i was ill and not being myself. having said that
column4: what do you mean by not being yourself? you could just be tired and weak and you aren't yourself...well in case when i say that i'm not myself means i totally become someone else and her name was molly. this is my body and mind defense mechanism. it actually tells people around me that my brain is overwhelmed and over stimulated. usually what happen is that i would faint and wake up tired but in special cases like the whole of last week
column5: i fainted and woke up as molly. it was hard at first to manage molly because she was a person full of high expectation
column7: very productive and determined to get things done and get it done fast. molly
column8: was my alternate ego. i wrote about her when i was in uni at australia and somehow it manifested through me and i became molly.

column1: although i think that she was a good worker
column2: but in reality she is not a real person and azhar thinks it is not a good idea to let molly go to work in this world. so when molly appeared
column3: azhar tends to talk to her
column4: reason with her and tell her to go back to her world. eventually molly got the picture and hasn't comeback since. my disassociations and having different parts of my personalities or time-age reappear are normal when i was very sick before
column5: and molly isn't the first one to come out. there were many different ones before this.. that's the wrap of my week. i was molly for a little while and i'm back to being izza ahmad. a woman with bipolar

column8: was my alternate ego. i wrote about her when i was in uni at australia and somehow it manifested through me and i became molly.

column1: although i think that she was a good worker
column2: but in reality she is not a real person and azhar thinks it is not a good idea to let molly go to work in this world. so when molly appeared
column3: azhar tends to talk to her
column4: reason with her and tell her to go back to her world. eventually molly got the picture and hasn't comeback since. my disassociations and having different parts of my personalities or time-age reappear are normal when i was very sick before
column5: and molly is not the first one to come out. there were many different ones before this.. that's the wrap of my week. i was molly for a little while and i am back to being izza ahmad. a woman with bipolar

column2: she and i had a lot of things in common
column3: one of them is making ""list"". having a list is very very very important to me as i need to write all of my worries down on paper. as my shrink said
column4: write it down so you can think of things logically.

column1: currently here are some of my list;
3. my learning ""how to do work"" list
5. how to get dad to be healthier
6. what i should do pending list
7. what azhar should do pending list
so you see these are just my top 10 list of things to do
column3: pending and so on. most important thing to note here is that
column4: if things are not checked off the list it would continuously be hovering in my mind. consequently
column5: my mind would get cluttered and the filing systems that i have created would disappear and information would spread off like wildfire. imagine a whole bunch of pigeons that was in their cages and some random dude came and decide to open the cage and let them loose. fly birdy fly...... having said that
column6: not everybody is like me and not everyone around me like having list hovering them everyday. that is the nature of life
column7: i understand but sometime when there are just too many stimulus and my list isn't progressing my brain went into the defense mode. that is what happen to me last week. i hope it doesn't happen again anytime soon because it seem really unfair to those people affected especially azhar
column8: but deep inside if it does happen again
column9: i hope i could manage it better.
